2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"61\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"37\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"90\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"98\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"98\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"106\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"106\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["Cats","Dogs","Equal","Not shown"],"a":1,"e":"Dogs have 8 marks, Cats have 3. Dogs have more.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which row has exactly one crossed group? <svg width=\"280\" height=\"104\" viewBox=\"0 0 280 104\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"6\" y=\"12\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">A:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"46\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">B:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"61\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"37\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"90\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"98\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"98\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"106\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"106\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"114\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"114\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"88\" y1=\"61\" x2=\"114\" y2=\"37\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"80\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">C:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["A","B","C","A and C"],"a":0,"e":"A = 5 = exactly one crossed group of 5.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many tally marks are shown? <svg width=\"113\" height=\"30\" viewBox=\"0 0 113 30\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"5\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"13\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"13\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"21\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"29\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"45\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"53\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"53\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"61\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"61\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"69\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"69\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"43\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"69\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"85\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"85\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"93\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"93\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"101\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"101\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["10","11","12","13"],"a":3,"e":"2 crossed groups (10) + 3 extra marks = 13.","d":"h"},{"t":"A bar graph shows 12 apples and 18 oranges. How many fruits in all?","o":["20","28","30","32"],"a":2,"e":"12 + 18 = 30 fruits total.","d":"e"},{"t":"A tally chart shows 25 votes for cats and 13 for dogs. How many more chose cats?","o":["10","12","14","38"],"a":1,"e":"25 − 13 = 12 more votes for cats.","d":"e"},{"t":"In a pictograph, each picture = 2 students. There are 5 pictures. How many students?","o":["5","7","10","15"],"a":2,"e":"5 pictures × 2 = 10 students. Skip count: 2, 4, 6, 8, 10.","d":"e"},{"t":"A tally chart shows how many pets students have. Dogs: IIII II, Cats: III, Fish: IIII. How many students have dogs?","o":["5","6","7","8"],"a":2,"e":"IIII is 5 and II is 2 more. 5 + 2 = 7 students have dogs.","d":"e"},{"t":"Look at the bar graph of favorite fruits. The bar for grapes goes up to 6. How many students chose grapes?","o":["4","5","6","7"],"a":2,"e":"The bar for grapes stops at 6, so 6 students chose grapes.","d":"e"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Cats IIII, Birds III, Fish II. Which pet got the most votes?","o":["Birds","Fish","Cats","They are all the same"],"a":2,"e":"Cats = 4, Birds = 3, Fish = 2. Cats got the most with 4 votes.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows favorite drinks: Milk=4, Juice=9, Water=5. Which drink has the tallest bar?","o":["Milk","Juice","Water","They are the same"],"a":1,"e":"Juice has 9 votes, which is the most, so it has the tallest bar.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Chocolate III, Vanilla IIII, Strawberry IIII I. How many students chose strawberry?","o":["4","5","6","3"],"a":2,"e":"IIII is 5 and I is 1 more. 5 + 1 = 6 students chose strawberry.","d":"e"},{"t":"Look at the bar graph of favorite sports. Soccer=5, Baseball=3, Basketball=7. Which sport has the shortest bar?","o":["Soccer","Baseball","Basketball","They are all the same"],"a":1,"e":"Baseball has only 3 votes, which is the fewest, so it has the shortest bar.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows favorite snacks: Crackers IIII, Fruit III, Pretzels IIII III. Which snack got the fewest votes?","o":["Crackers","Fruit","Pretzels","Crackers and Fruit"],"a":1,"e":"Crackers = 4, Fruit = 3, Pretzels = 8. Fruit has the fewest votes with only 3.","d":"e"},{"t":"The bar graph shows books read: Mia=8, James=5, Sofia=8. Which two students read the same number of books?","o":["Mia and James","James and Sofia","Mia and Sofia","No one matched"],"a":2,"e":"Mia and Sofia both read 8 books, so their bars are the same height.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows how students get to school: Walk IIII, Bus IIII III, Car III. How many students take the bus?","o":["5","6","7","8"],"a":3,"e":"IIII is 5 and III is 3 more. 5 + 3 = 8 students take the bus.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows stickers earned: Monday=2, Tuesday=6, Wednesday=1. On which day were the fewest stickers earned?","o":["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","They are all the same"],"a":2,"e":"Wednesday has only 1 sticker, which is the least. Its bar is the shortest.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Puppies IIII III, Kittens IIII II, Hamsters III. How many students voted for kittens?","o":["5","7","8","3"],"a":1,"e":"IIII is 5 and II is 2 more. 5 + 2 = 7 students voted for kittens.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows animals at a zoo: Monkeys=6, Penguins=6, Zebras=4. Which two animals have the same number?","o":["Monkeys and Zebras","Penguins and Zebras","Monkeys and Penguins","None are the same"],"a":2,"e":"Monkeys and Penguins both have 6, so their bars are the same height.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart is missing some data. Dogs: IIII, Cats: ???, Fish: III. You know 5 students voted for cats. Which tally should go in the cats row?","o":["IIII","III","IIII I","IIII II"],"a":2,"e":"Five tally marks is written as IIII I (the fifth line crosses through the first four). That equals 5.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows rainy days: March=2, April=5, May=3. How many rainy days were there in April?","o":["2","3","5","10"],"a":2,"e":"April's bar goes up to 5. That means there were 5 rainy days in April.","d":"e"},{"t":"A tally chart shows favorite seasons: Spring III, Summer IIII I, Fall IIII, Winter II. Which season got exactly 4 votes?","o":["Spring","Summer","Fall","Winter"],"a":2,"e":"Spring = 3, Summer = 6, Fall = 4, Winter = 2. Fall is the one with exactly 4.","d":"e"},{"t":"The bar graph shows toys sold: Dolls=3, Cars=7, Blocks=5. Put the toys in order from fewest sold to most sold.","o":["Cars, Blocks, Dolls","Dolls, Blocks, Cars","Blocks, Dolls, Cars","Dolls, Cars, Blocks"],"a":1,"e":"Dolls = 3 (fewest), Blocks = 5 (middle), Cars = 7 (most). Order: Dolls, Blocks, Cars.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Red IIII I, Blue III, Green IIII. How many votes does blue have?","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":0,"e":"Count the tally marks for blue: III = 3 votes.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows flowers in a garden: Roses=4, Tulips=7, Daisies=4. How many types of flowers have the same number?","o":["0","1","2","3"],"a":2,"e":"Roses and Daisies both have 4. That is 2 types of flowers with the same number.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Tigers III, Lions IIII, Bears IIII II. Which animal got the fewest votes?","o":["Tigers","Lions","Bears","Lions and Tigers"],"a":0,"e":"Tigers = 3, Lions = 4, Bears = 7. Tigers got the fewest with only 3.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows crayons in a box: Red=5, Blue=8, Yellow=3, Green=5. How many colors have exactly 5 crayons?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"Red = 5 and Green = 5. Two colors have exactly 5 crayons.","d":"m"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Pizza=9, Tacos=4, Burgers=6. How many more students voted for pizza than tacos?","o":["3","4","5","13"],"a":2,"e":"Pizza has 9 and tacos has 4. 9 - 4 = 5 more students voted for pizza.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Apples IIII III, Oranges IIII, Bananas IIII I. How many students voted for apples and bananas together?","o":["12","13","14","9"],"a":2,"e":"Apples = 8 and Bananas = 6. 8 + 6 = 14 students voted for apples and bananas together.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Red=7, Blue=7, Green=3, Yellow=5. Which two colors got the same number of votes?","o":["Red and Green","Blue and Yellow","Red and Blue","Green and Yellow"],"a":2,"e":"Red and Blue both have 7 votes. They got the same number.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Soccer IIII II, Baseball III, Basketball IIII IIII. How many fewer students chose baseball than basketball?","o":["3","5","6","7"],"a":2,"e":"Basketball = 9 and Baseball = 3. 9 - 3 = 6 fewer students chose baseball.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Dogs=10, Cats=6, Fish=4. How many students voted in all?","o":["16","18","20","14"],"a":2,"e":"Add them all: 10 + 6 + 4 = 20 students voted in all.","d":"e"},{"t":"A tally chart shows some favorite colors, but the green row is smudged. Red: IIII, Blue: III. There were 12 votes total. How many voted for green?","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"Red = 4 and Blue = 3, so that is 7. The total is 12. 12 - 7 = 5 voted for green.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Swings=8, Slide=5, Monkey Bars=8. Put the playground equipment in order from most popular to least popular.","o":["Slide, Monkey Bars, Swings","Swings, Slide, Monkey Bars","Swings and Monkey Bars (tie), then Slide","Slide, Swings, Monkey Bars"],"a":2,"e":"Swings and Monkey Bars both have 8 (tied for most), and Slide has 5 (least).","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Milk IIII, Juice IIII III, Water IIII II. Which drink got more votes than milk but fewer than juice?","o":["Milk","Juice","Water","None of them"],"a":2,"e":"Milk = 4, Water = 7, Juice = 8. Water (7) is more than Milk (4) but fewer than Juice (8).","d":"e"},{"t":"Mrs. Lee's class made a bar graph. Chocolate=11, Vanilla=6, Strawberry=3. How many more voted for chocolate than strawberry?","o":["5","6","8","14"],"a":2,"e":"Chocolate = 11 and Strawberry = 3. 11 - 3 = 8 more voted for chocolate.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Spring III, Summer IIII IIII, Fall IIII, Winter II. How many students voted for spring and winter combined?","o":["4","5","6","7"],"a":1,"e":"Spring = 3 and Winter = 2. 3 + 2 = 5 students voted for spring and winter combined.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Lions=5, Tigers=9, Bears=7. If 3 more kids vote for bears, how many votes would bears have?","o":["9","10","7","12"],"a":1,"e":"Bears has 7 now. 7 + 3 = 10. Bears would have 10 votes.","d":"m"},{"t":"The bar graph is missing data. Roses=6, Tulips=???, Daisies=4. There are 15 votes in all. How many votes did tulips get?","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"Roses + Daisies = 6 + 4 = 10. Total is 15. 15 - 10 = 5 votes for tulips.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Bikes IIII III, Scooters IIII, Skateboards IIII I. Do bikes and skateboards together have more or fewer votes than 15?","o":["More","Fewer","Exactly 15","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"Bikes = 8, Skateboards = 6. 8 + 6 = 14. 14 is fewer than 15.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Sunny=7, Rainy=2, Cloudy=5. How many more days were sunny than rainy?","o":["3","4","5","9"],"a":2,"e":"Sunny = 7 and Rainy = 2. 7 - 2 = 5 more days were sunny.","d":"e"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Crayons IIII II, Markers IIII I, Colored Pencils IIII IIII. Which supply is the second most popular?","o":["Crayons","Markers","Colored Pencils","Crayons and Markers are tied"],"a":0,"e":"Colored Pencils = 9 (most), Crayons = 7 (second), Markers = 6 (least). Crayons is second.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Math=6, Reading=4, Science=8. How many students voted for math and reading combined?","o":["8","10","12","14"],"a":1,"e":"Math = 6 and Reading = 4. 6 + 4 = 10 students combined.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Pepperoni IIII IIII, Cheese IIII III, Veggie III. How many more voted for pepperoni than veggie?","o":["5","6","7","8"],"a":1,"e":"Pepperoni = 9 and Veggie = 3. 9 - 3 = 6 more voted for pepperoni.","d":"e"},{"t":"Marcus says the bar graph shows Dogs=10, Cats=7. He says 2 more students picked dogs than cats. Is he right?","o":["Yes, 2 more","No, 3 more","No, 17 more","No, the same number"],"a":1,"e":"10 - 7 = 3. Marcus is wrong. There are 3 more, not 2 more.","d":"m"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Trucks=4, Cars=8, Vans=4. Which two categories have the same number of votes?","o":["Trucks and Cars","Cars and Vans","Trucks and Vans","None are the same"],"a":2,"e":"Trucks = 4 and Vans = 4. They have the same number of votes.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Hamsters IIII, Rabbits IIII III, Guinea Pigs II. How many total students voted?","o":["12","13","14","15"],"a":2,"e":"Hamsters = 4, Rabbits = 8, Guinea Pigs = 2. 4 + 8 + 2 = 14 total students.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Red=8, Blue=12, Green=5. How many students voted in all? If 30 students are in the class, how many did NOT vote?","o":["25 voted, 5 did not","23 voted, 7 did not","25 voted, 7 did not","20 voted, 10 did not"],"a":0,"e":"Total votes: 8 + 12 + 5 = 25. Students who did not vote: 30 - 25 = 5.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Apples IIII III, Oranges IIII, Grapes ???. There were 20 votes total. How many students voted for grapes?","o":["6","7","8","9"],"a":2,"e":"Apples = 8, Oranges = 4. That is 12. Total is 20, so 20 - 12 = 8 voted for grapes.","d":"m"},{"t":"Sam looks at a bar graph showing: Pizza=9, Tacos=5, Burgers=6. Sam says pizza got 3 more votes than burgers. What did Sam do wrong?","o":["Sam counted the tacos bar instead","Sam subtracted wrong: 9 - 6 = 3 is correct","Sam read the pizza bar wrong","Sam added instead of subtracted"],"a":1,"e":"9 - 6 = 3. Sam is actually correct! Pizza did get 3 more votes than burgers.","d":"h"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Dogs IIII II, Cats IIII I, Fish III. Maya says cats and fish together got more votes than dogs. Is she right?","o":["Yes, 9 is more than 7","No, 9 is less than 7","No, they are the same","Yes, 10 is more than 7"],"a":0,"e":"Dogs = 7. Cats = 6, Fish = 3, so Cats + Fish = 9. Yes, 9 is more than 7. Maya is right.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Soccer=8, Baseball=5, Basketball=11. Liam says the total is 22. What mistake did Liam make?","o":["He forgot to add baseball","He added wrong: the total is 24","He counted soccer twice","He read basketball as 10"],"a":2,"e":"8 + 5 + 11 = 24, not 22. It looks like Liam may have counted soccer (8) twice: 8 + 8 + 5 = 21, or misread a number.","d":"h"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Chocolate IIII IIII, Vanilla IIII II, Strawberry IIII. 24 students are in the class. How many did NOT vote?","o":["2","3","4","5"],"a":2,"e":"Chocolate = 9, Vanilla = 7, Strawberry = 4. Total = 20. 24 - 20 = 4 did not vote.","d":"m"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Swimming=7, Running=4, Biking=9. If 2 students change their vote from biking to running, what would the new totals for biking and running be?","o":["Biking=7, Running=6","Biking=11, Running=2","Biking=7, Running=4","Biking=9, Running=6"],"a":0,"e":"Biking loses 2: 9 - 2 = 7. Running gains 2: 4 + 2 = 6. New totals: Biking=7, Running=6.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Lions IIII I, Tigers IIII III, Bears IIII. Emma says tigers got twice as many votes as bears. Is she correct?","o":["Yes, 8 is double 4","No, 8 is not double 4","No, tigers got 7 votes","Yes, 6 is double 3"],"a":0,"e":"Tigers = 8, Bears = 4. Double of 4 is 8. Yes, Emma is correct!","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Spring=3, Summer=10, Fall=5, Winter=2. How many voted for the two least popular seasons combined? Is that more or less than summer alone?","o":["5, less than summer","7, less than summer","5, more than summer","12, more than summer"],"a":0,"e":"Spring = 3, Winter = 2 (two least popular). 3 + 2 = 5. Summer = 10. 5 is less than 10.","d":"m"},{"t":"Students made a tally chart about recess games. Tag: IIII III, Kickball: IIII, Four Square: ???. The teacher says 18 students voted. How many chose four square?","o":["4","5","6","7"],"a":2,"e":"Tag = 8, Kickball = 4, total so far = 12. 18 - 12 = 6 chose four square.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Crayons=6, Markers=9, Colored Pencils=5. Jake says markers got 3 more votes than colored pencils. Ava says markers got 4 more. Who is right?","o":["Jake is right","Ava is right","They are both right","Neither is right"],"a":1,"e":"9 - 5 = 4. Ava is right. Markers got 4 more votes than colored pencils.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Bikes IIII IIII, Scooters IIII I, Skateboards III. Could you split the bike votes evenly into 2 groups? Why or why not?","o":["Yes, 9 splits into 4 and 5","No, 9 is odd so it cannot split evenly","Yes, 9 splits into 3 groups of 3","No, you cannot split votes"],"a":1,"e":"Bikes = 9. 9 is an odd number, so it cannot be split into 2 equal groups. 4 + 5 = 9 but 4 and 5 are not equal.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Pepperoni=11, Cheese=7, Veggie=2. The class has 25 students. How many students were absent or did not vote?","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"Total votes: 11 + 7 + 2 = 20. 25 - 20 = 5 students were absent or did not vote.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Sunny IIII IIII I, Rainy IIII, Snowy II. Noah says sunny got 10 votes. What did Noah do wrong?","o":["Noah counted right, sunny is 10","Noah miscounted: sunny is 11","Noah read the rainy row","Noah forgot to count the I at the end"],"a":1,"e":"IIII = 5, IIII = 5, I = 1. 5 + 5 + 1 = 11. Noah likely missed the last tally mark. Sunny is 11, not 10.","d":"h"},{"t":"Two classes made bar graphs. Class A: Dogs=8, Cats=6. Class B: Dogs=5, Cats=9. Which class had more total votes for pets?","o":["Class A with 14","Class B with 14","They are the same with 14 each","Class B with 15"],"a":2,"e":"Class A: 8 + 6 = 14. Class B: 5 + 9 = 14. They are the same! Both had 14 total votes.","d":"m"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Red=6, Blue=4, Green=8, Yellow=2. How many students voted for a color that got fewer than 5 votes?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":2,"e":"Blue = 4 and Yellow = 2 both got fewer than 5. 4 + 2 = 6 students.","d":"m"},{"t":"A tally chart shows: Carrots III, Corn IIII II, Peas IIII. Carlos says corn got twice as many votes as carrots. What should Carlos check?","o":["If 7 is double 3 (it is not, double 3 is 6)","If 7 is double 4 (it is not)","If 4 is double 3 (it is not)","Nothing, Carlos is correct"],"a":0,"e":"Corn = 7, Carrots = 3. Double of 3 is 6, not 7. Carlos is wrong: 7 is not double 3.","d":"e"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Hiking=4, Camping=9, Fishing=7. If the teacher combines hiking and fishing into one bar called 'Outdoor Fun,' how tall would that bar be? Would it beat camping?","o":["11, yes it beats camping","11, no camping still wins","13, yes it beats camping","7, no camping still wins"],"a":0,"e":"Hiking + Fishing = 4 + 7 = 11. Camping = 9. 11 is more than 9, so yes, it beats camping.","d":"m"},{"t":"Maria made a tally chart but lost one row. She has: Cats IIII I, Birds III. She knows 15 students voted total. Her missing row is for dogs. How many voted for dogs?","o":["4","5","6","7"],"a":2,"e":"Cats = 6, Birds = 3, total = 9. There were 15 total, so 15 - 9 = 6 voted for dogs.","d":"m"},{"t":"A bar graph shows: Art=10, Music=6, PE=8. Riley says if 4 students switch from art to music, art and music would be tied. Is Riley right?","o":["No, art would have 6 and music 10","Yes, both would have 8","No, art would have 8 and music 8 but that ties with PE","No, both would have 7"],"a":0,"e":"Art: 10 - 4 = 6. Music: 6 + 4 = 10. Art=6, Music=10. They are NOT tied. Riley is wrong.","d":"m"}],"quiz":[{"t":"How many tally marks are shown? <svg width=\"65\" height=\"30\" viewBox=\"0 0 65 30\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"5\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"13\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"13\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"21\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"29\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"45\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"53\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"53\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["5","6","7","8"],"a":2,"e":"One crossed group (5) plus 2 more = 7."},{"t":"How many tally marks are shown? <svg width=\"81\" height=\"30\" viewBox=\"0 0 81 30\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"5\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"13\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"13\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"21\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"29\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"45\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"53\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"53\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"61\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"61\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"69\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"69\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["8","9","10","11"],"a":1,"e":"One crossed group (5) plus 4 more = 9."},{"t":"Which group has more tally marks? <svg width=\"280\" height=\"70\" viewBox=\"0 0 280 70\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"6\" y=\"12\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Dogs:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"90\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"98\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"98\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"46\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Cats:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"61\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"37\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["Dogs with 7","Cats with 5","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"Dogs have 7 marks, Cats have 5."},{"t":"What does this tally group equal? <svg width=\"49\" height=\"30\" viewBox=\"0 0 49 30\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin:0 4px\"><line x1=\"5\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"5\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"13\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"13\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"21\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"21\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"29\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"3\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"29\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"Four marks + diagonal cross = 5 total."},{"t":"How many total tally marks? <svg width=\"280\" height=\"138\" viewBox=\"0 0 280 138\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"6\" y=\"12\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Spring:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"90\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"98\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"98\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"46\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Summer:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"61\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"37\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"90\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"98\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"98\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"106\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"106\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"114\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"114\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"80\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Fall:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"95\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"71\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"114\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Winter:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"105\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"129\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"105\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"129\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"105\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"129\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["22","24","26","28"],"a":1,"e":"7 + 9 + 5 + 3 = 24 total."},{"t":"Which season was least popular? <svg width=\"280\" height=\"138\" viewBox=\"0 0 280 138\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"6\" y=\"12\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Spring:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"3\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"90\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"98\" y1=\"3\" x2=\"98\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"46\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Summer:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"61\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"37\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"90\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"98\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"98\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"106\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"106\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"114\" y1=\"37\" x2=\"114\" y2=\"61\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"80\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Fall:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"74\" y1=\"71\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"95\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"48\" y1=\"95\" x2=\"74\" y2=\"71\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><text x=\"6\" y=\"114\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Winter:</text><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"105\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"129\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"58\" y1=\"105\" x2=\"58\" y2=\"129\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/><line x1=\"66\" y1=\"105\" x2=\"66\" y2=\"129\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/></svg>","o":["Spring","Summer","Fall","Winter"],"a":3,"e":"Winter has the fewest tally marks (3)."}]},{"points":["Bar graphs show data using bars","TALLER bar = MORE","Read the number scale on the side","Compare bars to answer questions"],"examples":[{"c":"#229954","tag":"Pets in Our Class","p":"Reading a bar graph:","s":"<svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Favorite Pets Survey</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"91\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"71\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">6</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"31\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">8</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><rect x=\"35\" y=\"28\" width=\"40\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"55\" y=\"26\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">8</text><text x=\"55\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Dog</text><rect x=\"80\" y=\"48\" width=\"40\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#e67e22\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"100\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">6</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Cat</text><rect x=\"125\" y=\"18\" width=\"40\" height=\"90\" fill=\"#27ae60\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"145\" y=\"16\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">9</text><text x=\"145\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Fish</text><rect x=\"170\" y=\"68\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"