"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">B</text></svg>","o":["Cannot determine","Equal amounts","Graph is wrong","Scale is off"],"a":1,"e":"Both bars reach the same height — equal amounts!","d":"h"},{"t":"How many more dogs than birds? <svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Pet Survey</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"91\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"71\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">6</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"31\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">8</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><rect x=\"34\" y=\"48\" width=\"42\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#e67e22\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"55\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">6</text><text x=\"55\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Cats</text><rect x=\"89\" y=\"18\" width=\"42\" height=\"90\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"110\" y=\"16\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">9</text><text x=\"110\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Dogs</text><rect x=\"144\" y=\"78\" width=\"42\" height=\"30\" fill=\"#1abc9c\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"165\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">3</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Birds</text></svg>","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":3,"e":"Dogs (9) − Birds (3) = 6 more dogs.","d":"h"},{"t":"The scale counts by 2s. What value does the taller bar show? <svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Scale Example</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"91\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"71\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">6</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"31\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">8</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><rect x=\"45\" y=\"68\" width=\"55\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#3498db\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"72\" y=\"66\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">4</text><text x=\"72\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Low</text><rect x=\"130\" y=\"28\" width=\"55\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#e67e22\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"157\" y=\"26\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">8</text><text x=\"157\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">High</text></svg>","o":["4","6","8","10"],"a":2,"e":"Count: 1st=2, 2nd=4, 3rd=6, 4th=8. The taller bar = 8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which month had the fewest students? <svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Month Survey</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"91\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"71\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">6</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"31\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">8</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><rect x=\"34\" y=\"58\" width=\"42\" height=\"50\" fill=\"#3498db\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"55\" y=\"56\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">5</text><text x=\"55\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Jan</text><rect x=\"89\" y=\"28\" width=\"42\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#27ae60\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"110\" y=\"26\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">8</text><text x=\"110\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Feb</text><rect x=\"144\" y=\"78\" width=\"42\" height=\"30\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"165\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">3</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Mar</text></svg>","o":["Jan","Feb","Mar","Equal"],"a":2,"e":"March has the shortest bar (3) — the fewest.","d":"h"},{"t":"What makes a bar graph useful for comparing data? <svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Activity Survey</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"91\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"71\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">6</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"31\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">8</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><rect x=\"34\" y=\"48\" width=\"42\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#3498db\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"55\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">6</text><text x=\"55\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Mon</text><rect x=\"89\" y=\"18\" width=\"42\" height=\"90\" fill=\"#e67e22\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"110\" y=\"16\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">9</text><text x=\"110\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Tue</text><rect x=\"144\" y=\"68\" width=\"42\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#27ae60\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"165\" y=\"66\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">4</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Wed</text></svg>","o":["Uses pictures","Bars show amounts side by side","Uses a number line","Bars use colors only"],"a":1,"e":"Bars placed side-by-side make it easy to see at a glance which is more or less.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 1 student. The cat row has 5 stars. How many students picked cats?","o":["4","5","6","10"],"a":1,"e":"Each star means 1 student. There are 5 stars, so 5 students picked cats.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each smiley face = 1 vote. Dogs has 7 smiley faces and fish has 3. Which pet got more votes?","o":["Fish","They are the same","Dogs","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Dogs has 7 and fish has 3. 7 is more than 3, so dogs got more votes.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. The pizza row has 3 stars. How many students chose pizza?","o":["3","5","6","8"],"a":2,"e":"Each star = 2 students. 3 stars: skip count by 2: 2, 4, 6. That is 6 students.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each heart = 1 vote. Red has 4 hearts, Blue has 6 hearts, Green has 4 hearts. Which two colors got the same number?","o":["Red and Blue","Blue and Green","Red and Green","None are the same"],"a":2,"e":"Red = 4 and Green = 4. They both got 4 votes, so they are the same.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 kids. Soccer has 4 stars. How many kids picked soccer?","o":["4","6","8","10"],"a":2,"e":"Each star = 2 kids. 4 stars: 2, 4, 6, 8. That is 8 kids.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each circle = 1 student. Apples has 8 circles and bananas has 5 circles. Which fruit has fewer votes?","o":["Apples","Bananas","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"Bananas has 5 and apples has 8. 5 is less than 8, so bananas has fewer.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph uses a key that says each star = 5 students. The chocolate row has 2 stars. How many picked chocolate?","o":["2","5","7","10"],"a":3,"e":"Each star = 5 students. 2 stars: 5, 10. That is 10 students.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 1 vote. Summer has 9 stars. Winter has 3 stars. Spring has 6 stars. Which season has the most votes?","o":["Winter","Spring","Summer","They are all the same"],"a":2,"e":"Summer has 9, Spring has 6, Winter has 3. Summer has the most with 9 votes.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 votes. The blue row has 5 stars. How many votes did blue get?","o":["5","7","10","12"],"a":2,"e":"Each star = 2 votes. 5 stars: 2, 4, 6, 8, 10. That is 10 votes.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each ball = 1 student. Basketball has 6 balls and volleyball has 6 balls. Did the same number of students pick each sport?","o":["No, basketball has more","No, volleyball has more","Yes, they are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Basketball = 6 and Volleyball = 6. Yes, they are the same!","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 kids. Bikes has 3 stars. How many kids like bikes?","o":["3","8","10","15"],"a":3,"e":"Each star = 5 kids. 3 stars: 5, 10, 15. That is 15 kids.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 1 vote. Cats has 4 stars, Dogs has 7 stars, Birds has 2 stars. Which pet got the fewest votes?","o":["Cats","Dogs","Birds","They are all the same"],"a":2,"e":"Birds has only 2 stars. That is the fewest votes.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. The key says: each star = 2. You see 6 stars in the tiger row. How many students chose tigers?","o":["6","8","10","12"],"a":3,"e":"Each star = 2. There are 6 stars: 6 x 2 = 12 students chose tigers.","d":"e"},{"t":"Look at the pictograph. The key shows each apple picture = 1 student. The apple row has 3 pictures and the orange row has 5 pictures. How many picked oranges?","o":["3","4","5","8"],"a":2,"e":"Each picture = 1 student. The orange row has 5 pictures, so 5 students picked oranges.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 votes. Sunny has 4 stars and Cloudy has 2 stars. Which weather has more votes?","o":["Cloudy","They are the same","Sunny","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Sunny = 4 stars = 8 votes. Cloudy = 2 stars = 4 votes. Sunny has more.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. The candy row has 4 stars. How many students chose candy?","o":["4","9","15","20"],"a":3,"e":"Each star = 5. 4 stars: 5, 10, 15, 20. That is 20 students.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 1 kid. Swings has 8 stars, Slide has 5 stars, Sandbox has 3 stars. Put them in order from most to fewest.","o":["Sandbox, Slide, Swings","Swings, Slide, Sandbox","Slide, Swings, Sandbox","Swings, Sandbox, Slide"],"a":1,"e":"Swings = 8 (most), Slide = 5 (middle), Sandbox = 3 (fewest).","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Crayons has 3 stars. Markers has 3 stars. Do they have the same number of students?","o":["No, crayons has more","No, markers has more","Yes, both have 6 students","Yes, both have 3 students"],"a":2,"e":"Crayons: 3 x 2 = 6. Markers: 3 x 2 = 6. Yes, both have 6 students.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 1 student. The key is missing for one row. You know 4 students like turtles and you see 4 stars. What does each star equal?","o":["2 students","1 student","4 students","5 students"],"a":1,"e":"4 stars stand for 4 students. So each star = 1 student.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 votes. Trucks has 2 stars and Cars has 3 stars. Which has more votes?","o":["Trucks","They are the same","Cars","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Trucks = 2 x 5 = 10. Cars = 3 x 5 = 15. Cars has more votes.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Cats has 4 stars and Dogs has 6 stars. How many more students picked dogs than cats?","o":["2","4","8","12"],"a":1,"e":"Cats = 4 x 2 = 8. Dogs = 6 x 2 = 12. 12 - 8 = 4 more students picked dogs.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 votes. Pizza has 4 stars and Tacos has 2 stars. How many voted in all?","o":["6","20","30","10"],"a":2,"e":"Pizza = 4 x 5 = 20. Tacos = 2 x 5 = 10. 20 + 10 = 30 votes in all.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 kids. Red has 5 stars, Blue has 3 stars, Green has 4 stars. How many kids picked red and green together?","o":["9","14","18","24"],"a":2,"e":"Red = 5 x 2 = 10. Green = 4 x 2 = 8. 10 + 8 = 18 kids together.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. Soccer has 3 stars and Baseball has 1 star. How many fewer students picked baseball?","o":["2","5","10","20"],"a":2,"e":"Soccer = 3 x 5 = 15. Baseball = 1 x 5 = 5. 15 - 5 = 10 fewer picked baseball.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 votes. Chocolate has 7 stars and Vanilla has 5 stars. How many total votes for both flavors?","o":["12","14","20","24"],"a":3,"e":"Chocolate = 7 x 2 = 14. Vanilla = 5 x 2 = 10. 14 + 10 = 24 total votes.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Lions has 4 stars and Bears has 4 stars. How do they compare?","o":["Lions has more","Bears has more","They are the same with 8 each","They are the same with 4 each"],"a":2,"e":"Lions = 4 x 2 = 8. Bears = 4 x 2 = 8. They are the same with 8 students each.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 kids. The key says each star = 5. Swimming has 4 stars. Biking has 3 stars. How many more kids picked swimming?","o":["1","5","7","35"],"a":1,"e":"Swimming = 4 x 5 = 20. Biking = 3 x 5 = 15. 20 - 15 = 5 more kids.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 votes. Apples has 6 stars, Bananas has 2 stars, Grapes has 5 stars. Which fruit got the fewest votes, and how many?","o":["Apples with 12","Bananas with 4","Grapes with 10","Bananas with 2"],"a":1,"e":"Bananas = 2 x 2 = 4 votes. That is the fewest. (Apples = 12, Grapes = 10.)","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. Art has 3 stars and Music has 2 stars. The pictograph is missing data for PE. There were 30 students total. How many chose PE?","o":["5","10","15","20"],"a":1,"e":"Art = 3 x 5 = 15. Music = 2 x 5 = 10. That is 25. Total = 30. 30 - 25 = 5 students chose PE.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Bikes has 5 stars, Scooters has 3 stars, Skateboards has 4 stars. Put them in order from most to fewest students.","o":["Skateboards, Scooters, Bikes","Bikes, Skateboards, Scooters","Scooters, Skateboards, Bikes","Bikes, Scooters, Skateboards"],"a":1,"e":"Bikes = 10, Skateboards = 8, Scooters = 6. Order: Bikes, Skateboards, Scooters.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 votes. Spring has 2 stars and Summer has 5 stars. How many more voted for summer?","o":["3","10","15","35"],"a":2,"e":"Spring = 2 x 5 = 10. Summer = 5 x 5 = 25. 25 - 10 = 15 more voted for summer.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Roses has 6 stars and Tulips has 6 stars. Lily says they are different because roses are in a different row. Is Lily right?","o":["Yes, different rows means different totals","No, both have 12 students","Yes, roses always gets more","No, both have 6 students"],"a":1,"e":"Roses = 6 x 2 = 12. Tulips = 6 x 2 = 12. Same number of stars and same key means same total. Lily is wrong.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 kids. Carrots has 3 stars, Corn has 5 stars, Peas has 4 stars. How many kids voted in all?","o":["12","18","24","30"],"a":2,"e":"Carrots = 6, Corn = 10, Peas = 8. 6 + 10 + 8 = 24 kids in all.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. Cats has 3 stars and Dogs has 4 stars. How many students chose cats and dogs combined?","o":["7","15","20","35"],"a":3,"e":"Cats = 3 x 5 = 15. Dogs = 4 x 5 = 20. 15 + 20 = 35 students combined.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 votes. Sunny has 8 stars and Rainy has 3 stars. How many more votes did sunny get?","o":["5","10","11","22"],"a":1,"e":"Sunny = 8 x 2 = 16. Rainy = 3 x 2 = 6. 16 - 6 = 10 more votes for sunny.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 kids. Trucks has 2 stars, Cars has 4 stars, Vans has 1 star. Which two categories together equal 15?","o":["Trucks and Cars","Cars and Vans","Trucks and Vans","None equal 15"],"a":2,"e":"Trucks = 10, Vans = 5. 10 + 5 = 15. Trucks and Vans together equal 15.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Tigers has 5 stars and Elephants has 7 stars. What is the difference in students?","o":["2","4","12","24"],"a":1,"e":"Tigers = 5 x 2 = 10. Elephants = 7 x 2 = 14. 14 - 10 = 4 more for elephants.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 votes. The row for hiking has 3 stars. The row for camping has 5 stars. How many total votes?","o":["8","15","25","40"],"a":3,"e":"Hiking = 3 x 5 = 15. Camping = 5 x 5 = 25. 15 + 25 = 40 total votes.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 kids. Math has 4 stars and Science has 6 stars. How many more kids picked science?","o":["2","4","8","20"],"a":1,"e":"Math = 4 x 2 = 8. Science = 6 x 2 = 12. 12 - 8 = 4 more kids.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Hamsters has 3 stars, Rabbits has 5 stars, Fish has 2 stars. Which pet is in the middle (not most, not fewest)?","o":["Hamsters with 6 students","Rabbits with 10 students","Fish with 4 students","They are all the same"],"a":0,"e":"Fish = 4 (fewest), Hamsters = 6 (middle), Rabbits = 10 (most). Hamsters is in the middle.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Cats has 4 stars, Dogs has 6 stars, Birds has 3 stars. How many students voted in all? If the class has 30 students, how many did NOT vote?","o":["26 voted, 4 did not","26 voted, 6 did not","24 voted, 6 did not","22 voted, 8 did not"],"a":0,"e":"Cats=8, Dogs=12, Birds=6. Total=26. 30-26=4 did not vote.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. The cat row has 3 stars. Sam says that means 8 students chose cats. What did Sam do wrong?","o":["Sam added 5 + 3 instead of multiplying","Sam subtracted 5 - 3","Sam counted the stars wrong","Sam is correct"],"a":0,"e":"Each star = 5 students. 3 stars = 3 x 5 = 15. Sam added 5 + 3 = 8 instead of multiplying. That is wrong.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 votes. Red has 5 stars, Blue has 3 stars, Green has ???. There were 22 votes total. How many votes did green get?","o":["4","6","8","14"],"a":1,"e":"Red = 10, Blue = 6. That is 16. Total = 22. 22 - 16 = 6 votes for green.","d":"m"},{"t":"Could you make a pictograph with a key of each star = 3 for this data: Cats=9, Dogs=6, Fish=4? Why or why not?","o":["Yes, because all numbers are big enough","No, because 4 does not divide evenly by 3","Yes, because 3 goes into every number","No, because 9 is too large"],"a":1,"e":"Cats: 9 / 3 = 3 stars. Dogs: 6 / 3 = 2 stars. Fish: 4 / 3 = 1 star with 1 left over. You cannot show 4 evenly with a key of 3.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 kids. Soccer has 4 stars and Baseball has 2 stars. Emma says soccer got 10 more kids than baseball. Is she right?","o":["Yes, 20 - 10 = 10","No, the difference is 5","No, the difference is 2","No, the difference is 15"],"a":0,"e":"Soccer = 20, Baseball = 10. 20 - 10 = 10. Yes, Emma is right!","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Art has 7 stars, Music has 4 stars, Drama has 5 stars. Do music and drama together have more students than art?","o":["Yes, 18 is more than 14","No, 14 is more than 18","They are the same","No, 16 is more than 14"],"a":0,"e":"Art = 14. Music = 8, Drama = 10. Music + Drama = 18. 18 is more than 14. Yes!","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 votes. Bikes has 3 stars, Scooters has 2 stars, Skateboards has 4 stars. How many kids voted in all? What if 5 more kids vote for scooters -- how many stars would scooters have then?","o":["45 total, scooters would have 3 stars","35 total, scooters would have 3 stars","45 total, scooters would have 7 stars","35 total, scooters would have 7 stars"],"a":0,"e":"Bikes=15, Scooters=10, Skateboards=20. Total=45. Scooters would have 10+5=15 kids. 15/5=3 stars.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Dogs has 6 stars, Cats has 8 stars, Fish has 2 stars. Jake looks at the stars and says cats got 8 students. What mistake did Jake make?","o":["Jake forgot to multiply by 2","Jake counted the stars wrong","Jake looked at the wrong row","Jake is correct"],"a":0,"e":"Cats has 8 stars. Each star = 2. So cats = 8 x 2 = 16 students. Jake just counted stars instead of multiplying by the key.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. Chocolate has 4 stars, Vanilla has 3 stars. If the teacher wants to add a strawberry row with 10 students, how many stars should she draw?","o":["1 star","2 stars","5 stars","10 stars"],"a":1,"e":"Each star = 5 students. 10 students / 5 = 2 stars for strawberry.","d":"m"},{"t":"Could you make a pictograph with a key of each star = 2 for this data: Lions=8, Tigers=6, Bears=5? Why or why not?","o":["Yes, all numbers work with 2","No, because 5 does not divide evenly by 2","No, because 6 is too small","Yes, because 2 goes into every number"],"a":1,"e":"Lions: 8/2=4 stars. Tigers: 6/2=3 stars. Bears: 5/2=2 stars with 1 left over. 5 is odd, so it does not work with key=2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Two classes made pictographs about favorite fruits. Class A uses each star = 2. Class B uses each star = 5. Class A shows apples with 6 stars. Class B shows apples with 2 stars. Which class had more students pick apples?","o":["Class A with 12 students","Class B with 10 students","They are the same","Cannot tell without more info"],"a":0,"e":"Class A: 6 x 2 = 12. Class B: 2 x 5 = 10. Class A had more with 12 students.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 votes. Summer has 8 stars, Winter has 3 stars, Spring has 5 stars, Fall has 4 stars. Which two seasons together got exactly 16 votes?","o":["Summer and Winter","Spring and Fall","Winter and Spring","Summer and Fall"],"a":2,"e":"Summer=16, Winter=6, Spring=10, Fall=8. Winter + Spring = 6 + 10 = 16. Those two together got exactly 16 votes.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. Carrots has 2 stars, Corn has 4 stars, Peas has ???. There were 45 students total. How many stars should the peas row have?","o":["3 stars","5 stars","7 stars","9 stars"],"a":0,"e":"Carrots=10, Corn=20. That is 30. Total=45. 45-30=15 for peas. 15/5=3 stars.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 students. Puppies has 9 stars, Kittens has 6 stars. Mia says puppies got 12 more students than kittens. What should Mia check?","o":["She should multiply first: 18 - 12 = 6, not 12","She subtracted the stars: 9 - 6 = 3","She is correct","She should add instead"],"a":0,"e":"Puppies = 9 x 2 = 18. Kittens = 6 x 2 = 12. 18 - 12 = 6 more students, not 12. Mia should multiply first, then subtract.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 votes. Math has 3 stars, Reading has 5 stars. If 10 students switch from reading to math, how many stars would each row have?","o":["Math=5 stars, Reading=3 stars","Math=4 stars, Reading=4 stars","Math=13 stars, Reading=15 stars","Math=25 stars, Reading=15 stars"],"a":0,"e":"Math = 15, Reading = 25. Move 10: Math = 15+10 = 25. Reading = 25-10 = 15. 25/5 = 5 stars. 15/5 = 3 stars.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 kids. Hiking has 4 stars, Camping has 7 stars, Fishing has 3 stars. How many kids did the two least popular activities combined?","o":["7","14","22","28"],"a":1,"e":"Hiking = 8 (least), Fishing = 6 (second least). 8 + 6 = 14 kids combined.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. Bikes has 6 stars and Cars has 3 stars. Noah says the difference is 3 students. What did Noah do wrong?","o":["He subtracted stars instead of students: 6-3=3 stars, but the real difference is 15","He added instead of subtracted","He is correct","He read the wrong rows"],"a":0,"e":"Bikes = 30, Cars = 15. Difference = 30-15 = 15 students. Noah subtracted the stars (6-3=3) instead of the actual students.","d":"h"},{"t":"Can you make a pictograph with each star = 5 for: Roses=15, Tulips=10, Daisies=7? Why or why not?","o":["Yes, because all numbers are bigger than 5","No, because 7 does not divide evenly by 5","Yes, because 5 goes into 15 and 10","No, because 15 is too big"],"a":1,"e":"Roses: 15/5=3 stars. Tulips: 10/5=2 stars. Daisies: 7/5=1 star with 2 left over. 7 does not work with key=5.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 2 votes. Vanilla has 5 stars, Chocolate has 8 stars, Mint has 4 stars. There are 40 students in the class. How many did NOT vote?","o":["4","6","8","10"],"a":2,"e":"Vanilla=10, Chocolate=16, Mint=8. Total = 10+16+8 = 34. 40-34 = 6 did not vote.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pictograph shows each star = 5 students. Monkeys has 4 stars, Penguins has 2 stars, Pandas has 3 stars. If you changed the key to each star = 10, how many stars would monkeys need?","o":["2 stars","4 stars","8 stars","20 stars"],"a":0,"e":"Monkeys = 4 x 5 = 20 students. With key = 10: 20 / 10 = 2 stars.","d":"m"}],"quiz":[{"t":"Use the bar graph below. Which pet is most popular? <svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Favorite Pets Survey</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"91\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"71\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">6</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"31\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">8</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><rect x=\"35\" y=\"28\" width=\"40\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"55\" y=\"26\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">8</text><text x=\"55\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Dog</text><rect x=\"80\" y=\"48\" width=\"40\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#e67e22\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"100\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">6</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Cat</text><rect x=\"125\" y=\"18\" width=\"40\" height=\"90\" fill=\"#27ae60\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"145\" y=\"16\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">9</text><text x=\"145\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Fish</text><rect x=\"170\" y=\"68\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"190\" y=\"66\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">4</text><text x=\"190\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Bunny</text></svg>","o":["Dog","Cat","Bunny","Fish"],"a":3,"e":"Fish bar is tallest at 9."},{"t":"Use the bar graph below. How many more chose Dog than Bunny? <svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Favorite Pets Survey</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"91\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"71\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">6</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"31\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">8</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><rect x=\"35\" y=\"28\" width=\"40\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"55\" y=\"26\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">8</text><text x=\"55\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Dog</text><rect x=\"80\" y=\"48\" width=\"40\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#e67e22\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"100\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">6</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Cat</text><rect x=\"125\" y=\"18\" width=\"40\" height=\"90\" fill=\"#27ae60\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"145\" y=\"16\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">9</text><text x=\"145\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Fish</text><rect x=\"170\" y=\"68\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"190\" y=\"66\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">4</text><text x=\"190\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Bunny</text></svg>","o":["2","3","4","5"],"a":2,"e":"Dog: 8, Bunny: 4. 8 − 4 = 4 more."},{"t":"Use the bar graph below. Total students surveyed? <svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Favorite Pets Survey</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"91\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"88\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"88\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"71\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"68\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"68\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">6</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"48\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"48\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"31\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">8</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><rect x=\"35\" y=\"28\" width=\"40\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"55\" y=\"26\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">8</text><text x=\"55\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Dog</text><rect x=\"80\" y=\"48\" width=\"40\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#e67e22\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"100\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">6</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Cat</text><rect x=\"125\" y=\"18\" width=\"40\" height=\"90\" fill=\"#27ae60\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"145\" y=\"16\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">9</text><text x=\"145\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Fish</text><rect x=\"170\" y=\"68\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" rx=\"2\"/><text x=\"190\" y=\"66\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">4</text><text x=\"190\" y=\"117\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\">Bunny</text></svg>","o":["27","25","29","31"],"a":0,"e":"8 + 6 + 9 + 4 = 27."},{"t":"Use the bar graph below. Which sport is most popular? <svg width=\"520\" height=\"312\" viewBox=\"0 0 220 130\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"110\" y=\"12\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Favorite Sports</text><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"30\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"111\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">0</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"108\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"108\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"89\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">2</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/><text x=\"26\" y=\"66\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#666\">4</text><line x1=\"28\" y1=\"63\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"63\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><line x1=\"30\" y1=\"63\" x2=\"215\" y2=\"63\" stroke=\"#eee\" stroke-wid