Key is 5"],"a":1,"e":"No marks means nobody recorded that value.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line plot shows Apples: 4 marks, Bananas: 6 marks, Grapes: 2 marks. Most popular? <svg width=\"400\" height=\"216\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 108\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Fruit Survey</text><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"192\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"35\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"35\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"35\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#333\">Appl</text><text x=\"35\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"35\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"35\" y=\"50\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"35\" y=\"37\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"100\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"100\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"100\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">Ban</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"50\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"37\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"24\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"165\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"165\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"165\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">Grp</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"106\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#888\">Fruit</text></svg>","o":["Apples","Bananas","Grapes","Equal"],"a":1,"e":"Bananas have 6 marks — the most.","d":"h"},{"t":"How is a line plot different from a bar graph? <svg width=\"400\" height=\"216\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 108\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Line Plot</text><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"192\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"35\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"35\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"35\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">1</text><text x=\"35\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"100\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"100\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"100\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">2</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"50\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"165\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"165\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"165\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">3</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"106\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#888\">Value</text></svg>","o":["Bar graphs use numbers","Line plots use × marks on a number line","Bar graphs are bigger","Line plots use pictures"],"a":1,"e":"Line plots place × marks on a number line; bar graphs use bars.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line plot shows 6 marks total. 2 are above 3. How many above other numbers? <svg width=\"400\" height=\"216\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 108\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Line Plot</text><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"192\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"20\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"20\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"20\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">1</text><text x=\"20\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"73\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"73\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"73\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">2</text><text x=\"73\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"126\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"126\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"126\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">3</text><text x=\"126\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"126\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"179\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"179\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"179\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">4</text><text x=\"179\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"179\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"106\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#888\">Value</text></svg>","o":["2","3","4","5"],"a":2,"e":"6 − 2 = 4 marks above other numbers.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line plot shows test scores. Most marks are above 90. What can you conclude? <svg width=\"400\" height=\"216\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 108\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Test Scores</text><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"192\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"35\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"35\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"35\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">88</text><text x=\"35\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"100\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"100\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"100\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">90</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"50\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"165\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"165\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"165\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">92</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"165\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"106\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#888\">Score</text></svg>","o":["Most got below 90","Most got exactly 90","Most skipped","90 is lowest"],"a":1,"e":"Most marks above 90 means 90 was the most common score.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line plot: homework time 1:××, 2:×××, 3:×××, 4:×. Which times are tied? <svg width=\"400\" height=\"216\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 108\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Homework Time</text><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"192\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"20\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"20\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"20\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">1</text><text x=\"20\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"20\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"73\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"73\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"73\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">2</text><text x=\"73\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"73\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"73\" y=\"50\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"126\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"126\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"126\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">3</text><text x=\"126\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"126\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"126\" y=\"50\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"179\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"179\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"179\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">4</text><text x=\"179\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"106\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#888\">Hours</text></svg>","o":["1 and 4","2 and 3","1 and 2","3 and 4"],"a":1,"e":"Values 2 and 3 each have 3 marks — tied for most.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line plot shows 3 marks above 7. What does that tell us? <svg width=\"400\" height=\"216\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 108\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Line Plot</text><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"192\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"20\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"20\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"20\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">5</text><text x=\"20\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"73\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"73\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"73\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">6</text><text x=\"73\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"73\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"126\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"126\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"126\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">7</text><text x=\"126\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"126\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"126\" y=\"50\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"179\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"179\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"179\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">8</text><text x=\"179\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"106\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#888\">Value</text></svg>","o":["7 people surveyed","7 is most common","3 people chose 7","7 is the total"],"a":2,"e":"3 marks above 7 means 3 data points have the value 7.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line plot has values 2, 3, 4. Value 4 has no marks. What does the line plot show? <svg width=\"400\" height=\"216\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 108\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Line Plot</text><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"86\" x2=\"192\" y2=\"86\" stroke=\"#333\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><line x1=\"35\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"35\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"35\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">2</text><text x=\"35\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"35\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"100\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"100\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"100\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">3</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"76\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"63\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"50\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#229954\" font-weight=\"bold\">×</text><line x1=\"165\" y1=\"83\" x2=\"165\" y2=\"89\" stroke=\"#555\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"165\" y=\"99\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"9\" fill=\"#333\">4</text><text x=\"100\" y=\"106\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"7\" fill=\"#888\">Value</text></svg>","o":["Only data with marks is shown","4 was most common","4 is the key","All values must have marks"],"a":0,"e":"Line plots only show × marks where data exists; empty spots mean no one chose that value.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line plot shows X marks above each number. There are 4 X marks above the number 3. How many objects measured 3 inches?","o":["3","4","5","7"],"a":1,"e":"Each X mark means 1 object. There are 4 X marks above 3, so 4 objects measured 3 inches.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows X marks above numbers. There are 2 X marks above 5 and 6 X marks above 7. Which length has more objects?","o":["5 inches","They are the same","7 inches","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"5 inches has 2 X marks and 7 inches has 6 X marks. 6 is more, so 7 inches has more.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot about pencils shows: Above 4: X X X, Above 5: X X X X X, Above 6: X X. How many pencils are 5 inches long?","o":["3","4","5","2"],"a":2,"e":"Count the X marks above 5. There are 5 X marks, so 5 pencils are 5 inches long.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows: Above 2: X, Above 3: X X X X, Above 4: X X. Which length was measured the most?","o":["2 inches","3 inches","4 inches","They are all the same"],"a":1,"e":"3 inches has 4 X marks, which is the most. 3 inches was measured the most.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows 0 X marks above the number 6. How many crayons are 6 inches long?","o":["6","1","0","2"],"a":2,"e":"There are no X marks above 6. That means 0 crayons are 6 inches long.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows X marks about worm lengths. Above 1: X X X, Above 2: X X, Above 3: X X X X X. Which length has the fewest worms?","o":["1 inch","2 inches","3 inches","They are all the same"],"a":1,"e":"2 inches has only 2 X marks, which is the fewest.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows: Above 4: X X X, Above 5: X X X, Above 6: X X X. What can you say about the data?","o":["4 inches has the most","6 inches has the most","All three lengths have the same number","5 inches has the fewest"],"a":2,"e":"Each length has 3 X marks. They all have the same number of objects.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows how long ribbons are. Above 7: X X X X X X, Above 8: X X. How many ribbons are 7 inches long?","o":["2","5","6","8"],"a":2,"e":"Count the X marks above 7. There are 6, so 6 ribbons are 7 inches long.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows: Above 3: X X, Above 4: X X X X, Above 5: X. How many sticks are 4 inches long?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":3,"e":"Count the X marks above 4. There are 4, so 4 sticks are 4 inches long.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows shoe lengths. Above size 5: X X X, Above size 6: X X X. Do the same number of kids wear each size?","o":["No, size 5 has more","No, size 6 has more","Yes, they are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Size 5 has 3 X marks and size 6 has 3 X marks. They are the same!","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows: Above 1: X, Above 2: X X X X, Above 3: X X, Above 4: X X X. Which length has the most?","o":["1 inch","2 inches","3 inches","4 inches"],"a":1,"e":"2 inches has 4 X marks, which is the most.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows leaf lengths. Above 5: X X X X, Above 6: no X marks, Above 7: X X. Were any leaves 6 inches long?","o":["Yes, 6 leaves","Yes, 1 leaf","No, there were no 6-inch leaves","Cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"There are 0 X marks above 6. No leaves were 6 inches long.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows hand widths. Above 3: X X X X X, Above 4: X X X, Above 5: X X X X. Put the lengths in order from fewest to most X marks.","o":["3, 4, 5","4, 5, 3","4, 3, 5","5, 3, 4"],"a":1,"e":"3 inches = 5, 4 inches = 3, 5 inches = 4. From fewest to most: 4 (3 marks), 5 (4 marks), 3 (5 marks).","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows: Above 8: X X X X, Above 9: X, Above 10: X X. How many objects measured 9 inches?","o":["1","2","4","9"],"a":0,"e":"There is 1 X mark above 9. So 1 object measured 9 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot about bean lengths shows: Above 2: X X, Above 3: X X X X X X, Above 4: X X X. Which length was measured the most?","o":["2 inches","3 inches","4 inches","They are all the same"],"a":1,"e":"3 inches has 6 X marks, which is the most. 3 inches was measured the most.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows: Above 6: X X X, Above 7: X X X X X, Above 8: X X. How many strings are 8 inches long?","o":["3","5","2","8"],"a":2,"e":"Count the X marks above 8. There are 2, so 2 strings are 8 inches long.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows caterpillar lengths. Above 1: X X, Above 2: X X X, Above 3: X X X X. Which length has the fewest caterpillars?","o":["1 inch","2 inches","3 inches","They are all the same"],"a":0,"e":"1 inch has only 2 X marks, which is the fewest.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows: Above 4: X X X X, Above 5: X X X X. How many items are 4 or 5 inches long in total?","o":["4","5","8","9"],"a":2,"e":"4 inches has 4 marks and 5 inches has 4 marks. 4 + 4 = 8 items total.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows eraser widths. Above 1: X X X, Above 2: X X X X X, Above 3: X X. Which width was most common?","o":["1 inch","2 inches","3 inches","They are the same"],"a":1,"e":"2 inches has 5 X marks, which is the most. 2 inches was the most common width.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows: Above 5: X X, Above 6: X X X X, Above 7: X X X, Above 8: X. What is the smallest length shown with X marks?","o":["5 inches","6 inches","7 inches","8 inches"],"a":0,"e":"The smallest number with X marks above it is 5. So 5 inches is the smallest length.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows pencil lengths. Above 4: XX, Above 5: XXXXX, Above 6: XXX. Which length is most common?","o":["4 inches","5 inches","6 inches","They are all the same"],"a":1,"e":"5 inches has the most X marks (5). That means 5 inches is the most common length.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows ribbon lengths. Above 6: XXXX, Above 7: XXXX, Above 8: X. How many ribbons are there in all?","o":["4","8","9","12"],"a":2,"e":"Add the X marks: 4 + 4 + 1 = 9 ribbons in all.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows leaf lengths. Above 2: X, Above 3: XXXX, Above 4: XX, Above 5: XXX. How many more leaves are 3 inches than 4 inches?","o":["1","2","4","6"],"a":1,"e":"3 inches has 4 and 4 inches has 2. 4 - 2 = 2 more leaves at 3 inches.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows stick lengths from 2 to 6 inches. The shortest stick is 2 inches and the longest is 6 inches. What is the range?","o":["2 inches","4 inches","6 inches","8 inches"],"a":1,"e":"Range = longest - shortest = 6 - 2 = 4 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows hand spans. Above 4: XXX, Above 5: XXXXX, Above 6: XX. How many hands were measured in all?","o":["6","8","10","15"],"a":2,"e":"Add all the X marks: 3 + 5 + 2 = 10 hands were measured.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows crayon lengths. Above 3: XXX, Above 4: XXXXXX, Above 5: XX. Which length is least common?","o":["3 inches","4 inches","5 inches","They are all the same"],"a":2,"e":"5 inches has only 2 X marks, which is the fewest. 5 inches is least common.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows foot lengths. Above 7: XX, Above 8: XXXXXX, Above 9: XXX. How many fewer feet are 7 inches than 8 inches?","o":["2","3","4","6"],"a":2,"e":"8 inches has 6 and 7 inches has 2. 6 - 2 = 4 fewer at 7 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows string lengths. Above 3: XXXX, Above 4: X, Above 5: XXXX. Which two lengths have the same count?","o":["3 and 4","4 and 5","3 and 5","None are the same"],"a":2,"e":"3 inches has 4 and 5 inches has 4. They are the same!","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows flower heights from 1 to 4 inches. Above 1: X, Above 2: XXX, Above 3: XXXXX, Above 4: XX. What is the range?","o":["1 inch","2 inches","3 inches","4 inches"],"a":2,"e":"Tallest = 4 inches, shortest = 1 inch. Range = 4 - 1 = 3 inches.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows book widths. Above 5: XXX, Above 6: X, Above 7: XXXX, Above 8: XX. How many books were measured?","o":["4","7","10","14"],"a":2,"e":"3 + 1 + 4 + 2 = 10 books were measured.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows shell lengths. Above 2: XXXX, Above 3: XX, Above 4: XXXXX. How many more shells are 4 inches than 3 inches?","o":["1","2","3","7"],"a":2,"e":"4 inches has 5 shells and 3 inches has 2 shells. 5 - 2 = 3 more.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows marker lengths. Above 3: XX, Above 4: XXXXXXX, Above 5: XXX. How many markers are 4 inches or 5 inches long?","o":["7","9","10","12"],"a":2,"e":"4 inches = 7 and 5 inches = 3. 7 + 3 = 10 markers.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows twig lengths from 5 to 9 inches. Data only appears at 5, 7, and 9. The shortest is 5 and the longest is 9. What is the range?","o":["2 inches","4 inches","5 inches","9 inches"],"a":1,"e":"Range = longest - shortest = 9 - 5 = 4 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows feather lengths. Above 1: XXX, Above 2: XXXXX, Above 3: X. How many feathers in all?","o":["3","5","9","6"],"a":2,"e":"3 + 5 + 1 = 9 feathers in all.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows nail lengths. Above 1: XXXX, Above 2: XXXX, Above 3: XXXX. Are any lengths more common than others?","o":["Yes, 1 inch","Yes, 3 inches","Yes, 2 inches","No, they are all the same"],"a":3,"e":"Each length has 4 X marks. They are all the same, so no length is more common.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows bean lengths. Above 2: XX, Above 3: XXXXXX, Above 4: XXX. How many fewer beans are 2 inches than 3 inches?","o":["1","2","4","8"],"a":2,"e":"3 inches has 6 and 2 inches has 2. 6 - 2 = 4 fewer beans at 2 inches.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows worm lengths. Above 3: XXXX, Above 4: XX, Above 5: XXXXX. Which length is in the middle (not most, not fewest)?","o":["3 inches with 4 worms","4 inches with 2 worms","5 inches with 5 worms","They are all the same"],"a":0,"e":"4 inches = 2 (fewest), 3 inches = 4 (middle), 5 inches = 5 (most). 3 inches is in the middle.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows rock lengths. Above 4: XXX, Above 5: XXXXXXX, Above 6: XXXX. How many rocks in all?","o":["7","11","14","10"],"a":2,"e":"3 + 7 + 4 = 14 rocks in all.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows eraser widths. Above 1: XXXX, Above 2: XX, Above 3: XXXXX. What is the range?","o":["1 inch","2 inches","3 inches","5 inches"],"a":1,"e":"Biggest = 3 inches, smallest = 1 inch. Range = 3 - 1 = 2 inches.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows caterpillar lengths. Above 1: X, Above 2: XXX, Above 3: XXXXX. If you measured one more caterpillar and it was 1 inch, how many X marks would be above 1?","o":["1","2","3","5"],"a":1,"e":"1 inch currently has 1 X mark. Add 1 more: 1 + 1 = 2 X marks above 1.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows pencil lengths. Above 4: XX, Above 5: XXXXX, Above 6: XXX, Above 7: X. How many pencils are longer than 5 inches?","o":["1","3","4","9"],"a":2,"e":"Longer than 5 means 6 inches (3) and 7 inches (1). 3 + 1 = 4 pencils are longer than 5 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows leaf lengths. Above 2: XXX, Above 3: XXXXXX, Above 4: XX, Above 5: XXXX. How many leaves in all? What is the most common length?","o":["15 leaves, 3 inches most common","15 leaves, 5 inches most common","13 leaves, 3 inches most common","15 leaves, 2 inches most common"],"a":0,"e":"Total: 3+6+2+4 = 15 leaves. 3 inches has 6 X marks (the most), so it is the most common.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows stick lengths. Above 3: XXXX, Above 4: XX, Above 5: XXXXX, Above 6: XXX. Sam says 5 inches is the most common because 5 is the biggest number on the answer. What is wrong with Sam's thinking?","o":["Sam confused the length number with the count of X marks","Sam is correct","Sam should have picked 6 inches","Sam counted wrong"],"a":0,"e":"5 inches happens to have the most X marks (5), but Sam's reasoning is wrong. You find the most common by counting X marks, not by picking the biggest number on the line.","d":"h"},{"t":"A line plot shows ribbon lengths. Above 5: XXX, Above 6: XXXXXX, Above 7: XX, Above 8: XXXX. How many ribbons are 6 inches or longer?","o":["6","8","12","15"],"a":2,"e":"6 inches or longer: 6 (6) + 7 (2) + 8 (4) = 12 ribbons.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows hand spans. Above 4: XX, Above 5: XXXXX, Above 6: XXX. The class measured 15 hands total, but the line plot only shows 10. How many hands are missing from the plot?","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"Line plot total: 2+5+3=10. Class measured 15. 15-10=5 hands are missing.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows string lengths. Above 3: X, Above 4: XXX, Above 5: XXXXXX, Above 6: XX. How many strings are 4 inches or shorter?","o":["1","3","4","10"],"a":2,"e":"4 inches or shorter: 3 inches (1) + 4 inches (3) = 4 strings.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows flower heights. Above 6: XXX, Above 7: XXXXX, Above 8: XXXX, Above 9: XX. What is the range? How many flowers in all?","o":["Range 3, total 14","Range 4, total 14","Range 3, total 12","Range 2, total 14"],"a":0,"e":"Range: 9-6=3 inches. Total: 3+5+4+2=14 flowers.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows rock sizes. Above 1: XXXX, Above 2: XXX, Above 3: XXXXXX, Above 4: XX. If you remove all the 3-inch rocks, how many rocks are left?","o":["6","9","15","3"],"a":1,"e":"Total: 4+3+6+2=15. Remove the 6 rocks at 3 inches: 15-6=9 rocks left.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows bean lengths. Above 2: XX, Above 3: XXXXX, Above 4: XXX, Above 5: XXXX. Jada says more beans are shorter than 4 inches than longer than 4 inches. Is she right?","o":["Yes, 7 shorter vs. 4 longer","No, 4 longer vs. 7 shorter","They are the same","No, 5 shorter vs. 4 longer"],"a":0,"e":"Shorter than 4: 2 inches (2) + 3 inches (5) = 7. Longer than 4: 5 inches (4) = 4. Yes, 7 > 4. Jada is right.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows nail lengths. Above 1: XXX, Above 2: XXXXXXX, Above 3: XX. Could more students have measured 2-inch nails than 1-inch and 3-inch nails put together?","o":["Yes, 7 is more than 5","No, 5 is more than 7","They are the same","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"2-inch has 7. 1-inch + 3-inch = 3+2=5. Yes, 7 is more than 5!","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows twig lengths. Above 4: X, Above 5: XXXX, Above 6: XXXXXX, Above 7: XXX. Which two lengths together have exactly 7 twigs?","o":["4 and 5","5 and 6","4 and 6","5 and 7"],"a":3,"e":"5 inches (4) + 7 inches (3) = 7. Those two together make 7 twigs.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows feather lengths. Above 3: XXXX, Above 4: XX, Above 5: XXXXX, Above 6: XXX. How many feathers are NOT 5 inches?","o":["5","9","14","3"],"a":1,"e":"Total: 4+2+5+3=14. Take away the 5-inch ones: 14-5=9 feathers are not 5 inches.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows shoe sizes. Above 1: XXX, Above 2: XXXXX, Above 3: XXXX, Above 4: XX. Maria says size 2 is most common because she counted wrong and got 4. What is the correct count for size 2?","o":["3","4","5","6"],"a":2,"e":"Size 2 has XXXXX = 5 X marks. Maria miscounted. The correct count is 5, and size 2 IS the most common.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows caterpillar lengths. Above 2: XX, Above 3: XXXXXX, Above 4: XXXX. How many caterpillars are at least 3 inches long?","o":["6","10","4","12"],"a":1,"e":"At least 3 inches means 3 or more. 3 inches (6) + 4 inches (4) = 10 caterpillars.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows marker lengths. Above 5: XXX, Above 6: XXXXX, Above 7: X, Above 8: XXXX. If you add 3 more markers at 7 inches, would 7 inches be the most common?","o":["No, 7 inches would have 4, but 6 inches has 5","Yes, 7 inches would have 4 which is the most","No, 8 inches would still be more","Yes, 7 inches would have 3 which ties with 5 inches"],"a":0,"e":"7 inches currently has 1. Add 3: 1+3=4. But 6 inches has 5. 4 < 5, so no, 6 inches is still the most common.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows seed lengths. Above 1: XXXXX, Above 2: XXX, Above 3: XXXXXX, Above 4: XX. What is the range and total number of seeds?","o":["Range 3, total 16","Range 4, total 16","Range 3, total 14","Range 2, total 16"],"a":0,"e":"Range: 4-1=3. Total: 5+3+6+2=16 seeds.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows shell lengths. Above 3: XX, Above 4: XXXX, Above 5: XXXXXXX, Above 6: XXX. Leo says the range is 7 because the tallest column has 7 X marks. What did Leo confuse?","o":["Leo confused the range with the mode (most common count)","Leo is correct","Leo confused range with total","Leo read the wrong column"],"a":0,"e":"Range is about the spread of lengths, not the count. Range = 6-3 = 3 inches. Leo confused 'range' with the highest frequency (7 X marks).","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows eraser widths. Above 1: XXX, Above 2: XXXXXX, Above 3: XXXX, Above 4: X. How many erasers are wider than 2 inches?","o":["6","4","5","1"],"a":2,"e":"Wider than 2: 3 inches (4) + 4 inches (1) = 5 erasers.","d":"m"},{"t":"A line plot shows crayon lengths. Above 2: XXXX, Above 3: XXXX, Above 4: XXXX. All lengths have the same count. How many crayons in all? Can you say one length is more common?","o":["12 crayons, no length is more common","12 crayons, 4 inches is more common","8 crayons, no length is more common","12 crayons, 2 inches is more common"],"a":0,"e":"4+4+4=12 crayons. Each length has 4, so no length is more common than the others.","d":"e"},{"t":"A line plot shows worm lengths. Above 2: XXX, Above 3: XXXXX, Above 4: XXXX, Above 5: XX. A student adds one more worm. It is 3 inches. Now how many worms are 3 inches, and is 3 inches still the most common length?","o":["6 worms at 3 inches, yes still most common","5 worms at 3 inches, yes still most common","6 worms at 3 inches, no 4 inches took over","5 worms at 3 inches, tied with 4 inches"],"a":0,"e":"3 inches had 5, now has 5+1=6. 4 inches still has 4. 6 > 4, so 3 inches is still the most common.","d":"m"}],"quiz":[{"t":"Use the line plot below. How many students have 2 pets? <svg width=\"400\" height=\"216\" viewBox=\"0 0 200 108\" style=\"display:block;margin:8px auto;border-radius:8px;background:#f9f9f9\"><text x=\"100\" y=\"11\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"8\" fill=\"#333\" font-weight=\"bold\">Pets in Class</text><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"86\